  "original_lang": "ta",
  "original_title": "\u0b87\u0bb2\u0bb5\u0b9a\u0b95\u0bcd\u0b95\u0bb2\u0bcd\u0bb5\u0bbf \u0b9a\u0bc1\u0b95\u0bbe\u0ba4\u0bbe\u0bb0\u0ba4\u0bcd\u0ba4\u0bbf\u0bb1\u0bcd\u0b95\u0bbe\u0ba9 \u0b85\u0bb0\u0b9a \u0b89\u0ba4\u0bb5\u0bbf\u0b95\u0bb3\u0bc8 \u0b95\u0bc1\u0bb1\u0bc8\u0b95\u0bcd\u0b95\u0bc1\u0bae\u0bbe\u0bb1\u0bc1 \u0b9a\u0bb0\u0bcd\u0bb5\u0ba4\u0bc7\u0b9a \u0ba8\u0bbe\u0ba3\u0baf\u0ba8\u0bbf\u0ba4\u0bbf\u0baf\u0bae\u0bcd \u0ba8\u0bbf\u0baa\u0ba8\u0bcd\u0ba4\u0ba9\u0bc8 \u0bb5\u0bbf\u0ba4\u0bbf\u0b95\u0bcd\u0b95\u0bb2\u0bbe\u0bae\u0bcd - \u0baa\u0bbe\u0bb2\u0bbf\u0ba4 \u0b95\u0bcb\u0bb9\u0ba9",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "IMF may condition cuts in government aid for free education health - Palita Kohana",
      "author": "Rajeeban",
      "body_lines": [
        "The Sri Lankan Ambassador to China Palita Kohana said that the Asian Development Bank and the World Bank should contribute more to Sri Lanka's debt restructuring activities.",
        "Regarding debt relief, Sri Lanka and the International Monetary Fund have not yet reached an initial agreement, and the Asian Development Bank and the World Bank, which have given a lot of credit to Sri Lanka, are requested to present a plan that can accelerate the debt restructuring activities, Sri Lankan Ambassador to China Palita Kohana said in an exclusive interview to Global Times.",
        "He also said that his peers should provide more aid to the debt-ridden country amid ongoing conditions such as increasing protests, shortages of essential goods and the declaration of a state of emergency.",
        "At the end of last month the International Monetary Fund visited Sri Lanka for talks according to reports we received; We have appointed legal advisors in London and we have also appointed Western experts who understand debt restructuring, said Palita Kohana.",
        "But pointing out that the negotiations with the International Monetary Fund are still in the early stages, he said that once the new government takes office, new arrangements for the negotiations with the International Monetary Fund will be made.",
        "Palita Kohana mentioned that it is inevitable that the International Monetary Fund has to tighten us in every way - to control costs - to reduce, but in some cases it is difficult because we are at the end stage.",
        "We are concerned that the IMF may ask the government to cut funding to the health sector (free health care) as well as make recommendations on free education, which may cause further unrest.",
        "International financial institutions such as the World Bank, Asian Development Bank, etc. have given Sri Lanka a lot of funds. Wallread has also made significant investments. He appealed to these financial institutions to contribute more and expressed his expectation that the bilateral financial aid providers will also provide assistance to recover from the crisis Sri Lanka is facing.",
        "Polithagohana said that the protests against Ranilwickramasinghe in Sri Lanka are still going on and it is not known whether he will last long in the office of the acting president.",
        "He said that this is a very unsatisfactory situation because there is a sudden question about the leadership of the country and because of this constitutional arrangements should be followed and elections should be held to elect a new president within a specified period.",
        "Whatever government takes office, it will maintain good relations with China, Sri Lanka's main trading partner and investor, and the two countries have strategic ties. Any government that takes office after the elections will have the trust of China and the goodwill of the Chinese people, said Palita Kohana."
      ],
